cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software in your research, please cite it as below."
title: "AMP-Agent: An End-to-End LLM-Driven Platform for Autonomous Antimicrobial Peptide Design"
abstract: >
  AMP-Agent is an autonomous antimicrobial peptide (AMP) design platform that
  couples a large language model (Qwen) with a fleet of specialized
  microservices for generation, multi-objective evaluation, structural
  validation, and knowledge-guided feedback. The platform implements a fully
  automated loop from natural-language requirements to Pareto-ranked peptide
  candidates with 3D structural evidence.
type: software
authors:
  - name: "Chinfo Lab"
keywords:
  - antimicrobial peptide
  - AMP design
  - large language model
  - agentic AI
  - multi-objective optimization
  - Pareto ranking
  - ESMFold
  - retrieval-augmented generation
